explanation:
This question describes a single pass of the Bubble Sort algorithm. 
1. Compare 34 and 21: swap -> {21, 34, 78, 55, 11, 46}
2. Compare 34 and 78: no swap -> {21, 34, 78, 55, 11, 46}
3. Compare 78 and 55: swap -> {21, 34, 55, 78, 11, 46}
4. Compare 78 and 11: swap -> {21, 34, 55, 11, 78, 46}
5. Compare 78 and 46: swap -> {21, 34, 55, 11, 46, 78}
Because the highest number (78) will continuously swap with any smaller number to its right, one full pass guarantees that the highest number ends up at the very end of the list.
